-- 
Stocks Advance; Pearson Shares Lead FTSE 100 Index Higher in London Trade

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-06-09T15:20:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/stocks-advance-pearson-shares-lead-ftse-100-index-higher-in-london-trade.html
U.K. stocks climbed, with the
benchmark FTSE 100 Index rebounding from a two-month low, as
gains in media stocks and an analyst recommendation boosted  Weir
Group Plc. (WEIR)   Weir Group Plc rallied 4.7 percent after RBC Capital
Markets raised its price estimate on the shares and reiterated
it as one of the broker’s top picks.  WPP Plc (WPP) , the world’s
biggest advertising company, and  Pearson Plc (PSON)  both gained more
than 1 percent. Home Retail Group Plc tumbled 13 percent,
dragging retailers lower, as sales at Argos stores open at least
a year fell.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index gained 43.48, or 0.8 percent,
to 5,852.37 at 4:14 p.m. in London. Still, the measure has
fallen 2.3 percent this month as reports on U.S. employment and
factory orders added to concern that the economy is faltering.
The FTSE All-Share Index advanced 0.7 percent today,  To contact the reporter on this story:
